The paper proposes a novel hashing method for large-scale image retrieval using Convolutional Neural Network (CNN). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also focuses on retrieval tasks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also mentions the use of unsupervised learning, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with image datasets, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a new hashing method, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
